title: Whole Genome Sequencing of Genome In A Bottle HG002 Unsheared Genomic DNA using ONT.
design_description: Ultralong Oxford Nanopore sequencing of Genome in a Bottle Ashkenazi son cell line HG002 (GM24385) (Jain, et al 2018, https://doi.org/10.1038/nbt.4060). Sequencing was performed on 8/16/2017 at  the Joint Initiative for Metrology in Biology. DNA was prepared using various modified versions of Josh Quick's protocol (https://dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.mrxc57n). Sequencing was performed on the MinION using a FLO-MIN106 flowcell and SQK-RAD003 sequencing kit. Basecalling was performed using Guppy V3.2.4 (https://nanoporetech.com/) and dna_r9.4.1_450bps_hac.cfg configuration file. Reads were aligned to the human genome reference GRCh38 without alts or decoys (GCA_000001405.15_GRCh38_no_alt_analysis_set.fna.gz) using minimap2 (https://github.com/lh3/minimap2, Li 2018 https://doi.org/10.1093/bioinformatics/bty191).

Reads were aligned to the human genome reference GRCh38 without alts or decoys (GCA_000001405.15_GRCh38_no_alt_analysis_set.fna.gz) using minimap2 (https://github.com/lh3/minimap2, Li 2018 https://doi.org/10.1093/bioinformatics/bty191).

title: Whole Genome Sequencing of Genome In A Bottle HG002 Unsheared Genomic DNA using ONT.
design_description: Ultralong Oxford Nanopore sequencing of Genome in a Bottle Ashkenazi son cell line HG002 (GM24385) (Jain, et al 2018, https://doi.org/10.1038/nbt.4060). Sequencing was performed on 10/19/2018 at  Nick Loman's laboratory at the University of Birmingham. DNA was prepared using various modified versions of Josh Quick's protocol (https://dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.mrxc57n). Sequencing was performed on the GridION using a FLO-MIN106 flowcell and SQK-RAD004 sequencing kit. Basecalling was performed using Guppy V3.2.4 (https://nanoporetech.com/) and dna_r9.4.1_450bps_hac.cfg configuration file. Reads were aligned to the human genome reference GRCh38 without alts or decoys (GCA_000001405.15_GRCh38_no_alt_analysis_set.fna.gz) using minimap2 (https://github.com/lh3/minimap2, Li 2018 https://doi.org/10.1093/bioinformatics/bty191).
